  "body": "{\"query\":\"web.dev Core Web Vitals interaction to next paint cumulative layout shift largest contentful paint official\",\"follow_up_questions\":null,\"answer\":null,\"images\":[],\"results\":[{\"url\":\"https://www.corewebvitals.io/core-web-vitals\",\"title\":\"What Are the Core Web Vitals? LCP, INP & CLS Explained (2026)\",\"content\":\"Everything you need to know about the Core Web Vitals: metrics, thresholds, measurement tools, and how to pass them. **Core Web Vitals are three Google metrics that measure real user experience: Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) measures loading speed (good: under 2.5 seconds), Interaction to Next Paint (INP) measures responsiveness (good: under 200 milliseconds), and Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS) measures visual stability (good: under 0.1). The 3 metrics that make up the Core Web Vitals are: **Largest Contentful Paint** (LCP), **Interaction to Next Paint** (INP) and **Cumulative Layout Shift** (CLS). Google rates the Core Web Vitals of your site as *Good*, *Needs Improvement* or *Poor*. Google's Core Web Vitals are three metrics (**Largest Contentful Paint**, **Interaction to Next Paint** and **Cumulative Layout Shift**) that measure the user experience of a website. To pass the Core Web Vitals at least 75% of your visitors need to have a '**good**' LCP, INP and CLS score in the Google CrUX dataset on the URL level.\",\"score\":0.76490957,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://crystallize.com/answers/tech-dev/core-web-vitals\",\"title\":\"Understanding Core Web Vitals - Crystallize.com\",\"content\":\"What Is a Vertical Market? What Is a Mission Statement? What Is a Conversion Funnel? What Is First-Party Data? What is the Digital Product Passport? What Is a Product Mockup? What Are Product Data Sheets? What Is a Product SKU? What Is the Digital Shelf? What Is a Dynamic Content Block? What Are Product Performance Analytics? What Is a Load Balancer? What Is a Browser Cache? Core Web Vitals is a set of metrics introduced by Google that aim to help you measure the quality of user experience on a website. The three core web vitals metrics are the largest contentful paint, first input delay, and cumulative layout shift, and they measure the loading, interactivity, and visual stability of the webpage. **Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)** is a user-centric performance metric that measures the time it takes for the largest visible element on a web page to load and render on the screen fully.\",\"score\":0.67269784,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://web.dev/explore/learn-core-web-vitals\",\"title\":\"Core Web Vitals  |  web.dev\",\"content\":\"We are looking for web developers to participate in user research, product testing, discussion groups and more. ### Core Web Vitals. ## Learn Core Web Vitals. An initiative to provide unified guidance for quality signals that are essential to delivering a great user experience on the web. * #### The business impact of Core Web Vitals. * #### Optimizing Core Web Vitals for business decision makers. ### Core Web Vitals Metrics. * #### Interaction to Next Paint (INP). * #### Defining the Core Web Vitals metrics thresholds. ### Measure Core Web Vitals. * #### Core Web Vitals workflows with Google tools. * #### Best practices for measuring Web Vitals in the field. ### Debug Core Web Vitals. ### Improve Core Web Vitals. * #### Optimize Interaction to Next Paint. * #### The most effective ways to improve Core Web Vitals. ### Best practices. * #### Best practices for cookie notices. * #### Best practices for tags and tag managers.\",\"score\":0.5180835,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://web.dev/blog/inp-cwv\",\"title\":\"Advancing Interaction to Next Paint  |  Blog  |  web.dev\",\"content\":\"Learn about Chrome's plan to make it a Core Web Vital in 2024. Chrome's mission with the Web Vitals program is to help developers focus on the metrics that are essential to great user experiences—the Core Web Vitals. One important aspect of the user experience that we've been focusing on is responsiveness, which is the ability of a web page to react quickly to user interactions. First Input Delay (FID) is the Core Web Vital metric that measures responsiveness, but as we've written in the past, there are known limitations of FID. In 2022, we announced Interaction to Next Paint (INP) as that new metric, made it widely available in our tools, and started working with the community to test its efficacy. Graphic showing the timeline of INP phases, starting from when Chrome announced experimental support for INP in May 2022, to today in May 2023 when Chrome is announcing that INP is now a non-experimental, pending Core Web Vital metric, and finally to March 2024 when INP becomes a stable Core Web Vital metric, replacing FID.\",\"score\":0.3934089,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.enterspeed.com/blog/meet-the-new-core-web-vital-interaction-to-next-paint-inp\",\"title\":\"Meet the new Core Web Vital: Interaction to Next Paint (INP)\",\"content\":\"# Meet the new Core Web Vital: Interaction to Next Paint (INP). Thumbnail for blog post: Meet the new Core Web Vital: Interaction to Next Paint (INP). In March 2024, Interaction to Next Paint (INP) will replace one of the current Core Web Vitals, First Input Delay (FID). This is a big deal since Core Web Vitals affect both user experience and your organic rankings on Google (Core Web Vitals became a part of Google's ranking algorithm in 2021). *💡* *If you're already familiar with Core Web Vitals, you can skip to the \\\"Meet the new kid on the block: INP\\\"-section.*. ## What is core Web Vitals? **First Input Delay (FID):** FID measures the responsiveness of a webpage by quantifying the delay between a user's initial interaction (e.g., clicking a button) and the browser's ability to respond. Now let's look at the new Core Web Vital that will replace First Input Delay (FID): The new metric, Interaction to Next Paint (INP).\",\"score\":0.3492669,\"raw_content\":null},{\"url\":\"https://www.lumar.io/blog/industry-news/inp-interaction-to-next-paint-the-new-core-web-vitals-metric-seos-should-know\",\"title\":\"INP (Interaction to Next Paint): The New Core Web Vitals Metric SEOs Should Know - Lumar\",\"content\":\"Home / Lumar Blog: SEO, GEO/AEO, & Website Optimization Insights / Industry News - SEO / INP (Interaction to Next Paint): The New Core Web Vitals Metric SEOs Should Know. # INP (Interaction to Next Paint): The New Core Web Vitals Metric SEOs Should Know. INP will replace FID in Google’s Core Web Vitals metrics in March 2024. INP (Interaction to Next Paint): The New Core Web Vitals Metric. INP (Interaction to Next Paint) will replace FID (First Input Delay) in Google’s Core Web Vitals metrics on March 12, 2024. Google is evolving its Core Web Vitals metrics to replace its “First Input Delay” (FID) metric with “Interaction to Next Paint” (INP). **INP will offer a more comprehensive analysis of user experience than its FID predecessor, as it samples all interactions on the web page to make its assessment** — rather than looking only at a user’s first interaction on a page (as was the case with FID).\",\"score\":0.22805373,\"raw_content\":null}],\"response_time\":1.28,\"request_id\":\"241d0b2a-80c3-453f-a1bf-c1aadcff3db3\"}"
